                <h1>Discovering the Legacy of Goodwill Founder Edgar J. Helms</h1>
                <p>Goodwill's founder, Edgar J. Helms, launched the organization in 1902 to help individuals with disabilities and job barriers gain employment. By collecting donated goods, he created a pathway to job training and dignity for thousands. Helms' vision transformed lives, fostering self-sufficiency and community support through social enterprise.</p>
